{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":5364,"text":"In the 1980s, in communist\nEastern Germany,"},{"time":12089,"text":"if you owned a typewriter,"},{"time":15287,"text":"you had to register it\nwith the government."},{"time":18112,"text":"You had to register a sample sheet of text\nout of the typewriter."},{"time":23600,"text":"And this was done\nso the government could track"},{"time":27175,"text":"where the text was coming from."},{"time":28944,"text":"If they found a paper\nwhich had the wrong kind of thought,"},{"time":34663,"text":"they could track down\nwho created that thought."},{"time":39109,"text":"And we in the West"},{"time":41894,"text":"couldn't understand\nhow anybody would do this,"},{"time":44600,"text":"how much this would restrict\nfreedom of speech."},{"time":47801,"text":"We would never do that\nin our own countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53059,"text":"But today, in 2011, if you go\nand buy a color laser printer"},{"time":59500,"text":"from any major laser printer manufacturer"},{"time":63363,"text":"and print a page,"},{"time":64824,"text":"that page will end up"},{"time":66600,"text":"having slight yellow dots\nprinted on every single page,"},{"time":71844,"text":"in a pattern which makes the page unique\nto you and to your printer."},{"time":79121,"text":"This is happening to us today."},{"time":84098,"text":"And nobody seems\nto be making a fuss about it."},{"time":88355,"text":"And this is an example"},{"time":91043,"text":"of the ways our own governments\nare using technology"},{"time":97919,"text":"against us, the citizens."},{"time":101919,"text":"And this is one of the main three sources\nof online problems today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106277,"text":"If we look at what's really\nhappening in the online world,"},{"time":109291,"text":"we can group the attacks\nbased on the attackers."},{"time":112768,"text":"We have three main groups."},{"time":114600,"text":"We have online criminals."},{"time":116063,"text":"Like here, we have Mr. Dmitry Golubov,"},{"time":118290,"text":"from the city of Kiev in Ukraine."},{"time":121159,"text":"And the motives of online criminals\nare very easy to understand."},{"time":125600,"text":"These guys make money."},{"time":127218,"text":"They use online attacks\nto make lots of money --"},{"time":131496,"text":"and lots and lots of it."},{"time":133497,"text":"We actually have several cases\nof millionaires online, multimillionaires,"},{"time":138906,"text":"who made money with their attacks."},{"time":140690,"text":"Here's Vladimir Tsastsin,\nfrom Tartu in Estonia."},{"time":144216,"text":"This is [Albert] Gonzalez."},{"time":146035,"text":"This is Stephen Watt."},{"time":147834,"text":"This is Bjorn Sundin."},{"time":149656,"text":"This is Matthew Anderson, Tariq Al-Daour"},{"time":151621,"text":"and so on and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154996,"text":"These guys make their fortunes online,"},{"time":159239,"text":"but they make it through the illegal means"},{"time":161600,"text":"of using things like banking Trojans"},{"time":164319,"text":"to steal money from our bank accounts\nwhile we do online banking,"},{"time":167796,"text":"or with keyloggers"},{"time":170070,"text":"to collect our credit card information"},{"time":172352,"text":"while we are doing online shopping\nfrom an infected computer."},{"time":175937,"text":"The US Secret Service,"},{"time":178315,"text":"two months ago,\nfroze the Swiss bank account"},{"time":181361,"text":"of Mr. Sam Jain right here,"},{"time":183966,"text":"and that bank account\nhad 14.9 million US dollars in it"},{"time":187702,"text":"when it was frozen."},{"time":189117,"text":"Mr. Jain himself is on the loose;\nnobody knows where he is."},{"time":193377,"text":"And I claim it's already today"},{"time":197075,"text":"that it's more likely for any of us\nto become the victim of a crime online"},{"time":202821,"text":"than here in the real world."},{"time":206431,"text":"And it's very obvious\nthat this is only going to get worse."},{"time":209400,"text":"In the future, the majority of crime\nwill be happening online."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216228,"text":"The second major group of attackers\nthat we are watching today"},{"time":219600,"text":"are not motivated by money."},{"time":221883,"text":"They're motivated by something else --"},{"time":224010,"text":"motivated by protests,"},{"time":226011,"text":"motivated by an opinion,"},{"time":228247,"text":"motivated by the laughs."},{"time":230442,"text":"Groups like Anonymous\nhave risen up over the last 12 months"},{"time":235991,"text":"and have become a major player\nin the field of online attacks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241027,"text":"So those are the three main attackers:"},{"time":242883,"text":"criminals who do it for the money,"},{"time":244962,"text":"hacktivists like Anonymous\ndoing it for the protest,"},{"time":249485,"text":"but then the last group\nare nation states --"},{"time":252711,"text":"governments doing the attacks."},{"time":257291,"text":"And then we look at cases\nlike what happened in DigiNotar."},{"time":260808,"text":"This is a prime example of what happens\nwhen governments attack"},{"time":264718,"text":"against their own citizens."},{"time":267152,"text":"DigiNotar is a certificate\nauthority from the Netherlands --"},{"time":272163,"text":"or actually, it was."},{"time":273763,"text":"It was running into bankruptcy last fall,"},{"time":279009,"text":"because they were hacked into."},{"time":280801,"text":"Somebody broke in\nand they hacked it thoroughly."},{"time":285331,"text":"And I asked last week,"},{"time":287930,"text":"in a meeting with Dutch\ngovernment representatives,"},{"time":292077,"text":"I asked one of the leaders of the team"},{"time":296890,"text":"whether he found plausible\nthat people died"},{"time":302244,"text":"because of the DigiNotar hack."},{"time":306187,"text":"And his answer was: yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310813,"text":"So how do people die"},{"time":312876,"text":"as the result of a hack like this?"},{"time":315789,"text":"Well, DigiNotar is a CA."},{"time":317600,"text":"They sell certificates."},{"time":319600,"text":"What do you do with certificates?"},{"time":321230,"text":"Well, you need a certificate\nif you have a website"},{"time":323796,"text":"that has https, SSL encrypted services,"},{"time":328465,"text":"services like Gmail."},{"time":332103,"text":"Now we all, or a big part of us,\nuse Gmail or one of their competitors,"},{"time":335788,"text":"but these services are especially popular\nin totalitarian states like Iran,"},{"time":341600,"text":"where dissidents\nuse foreign services like Gmail"},{"time":346600,"text":"because they know they are more\ntrustworthy than the local services"},{"time":349815,"text":"and they are encrypted\nover SSL connections,"},{"time":352600,"text":"so the local government\ncan't snoop on their discussions."},{"time":356936,"text":"Except they can,"},{"time":358304,"text":"if they hack into a foreign CA\nand issue rogue certificates."},{"time":362179,"text":"And this is exactly what happened\nwith the case of DigiNotar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369849,"text":"What about Arab Spring"},{"time":371865,"text":"and things that have been happening,\nfor example, in Egypt?"},{"time":375200,"text":"Well, in Egypt,"},{"time":376567,"text":"the rioters looted the headquarters\nof the Egyptian secret police"},{"time":380298,"text":"in April 2011,"},{"time":382912,"text":"and when they were looting the building,\nthey found lots of papers."},{"time":386080,"text":"Among those papers\nwas this binder entitled, \"FinFisher.\""},{"time":389961,"text":"And within that binder were notes\nfrom a company based in Germany,"},{"time":394821,"text":"which had sold to the Egyptian government"},{"time":398367,"text":"a set of tools for intercepting,\nat a very large scale,"},{"time":403094,"text":"all the communication\nof the citizens of the country."},{"time":406169,"text":"They had sold this tool for 280,000 euros\nto the Egyptian government."},{"time":411069,"text":"The company headquarters are right here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414013,"text":"So Western governments are providing\ntotalitarian governments with tools"},{"time":418454,"text":"to do this against their own citizens."},{"time":422033,"text":"But Western governments\nare doing it to themselves as well."},{"time":425034,"text":"For example, in Germany,"},{"time":427229,"text":"just a couple of weeks ago,\nthe so-called \"State Trojan\" was found,"},{"time":431816,"text":"which was a Trojan used\nby German government officials"},{"time":435592,"text":"to investigate their own citizens."},{"time":437819,"text":"If you are a suspect in a criminal case,"},{"time":441547,"text":"well, it's pretty obvious,\nyour phone will be tapped."},{"time":444096,"text":"But today, it goes beyond that."},{"time":446362,"text":"They will tap your Internet connection."},{"time":448305,"text":"They will even use tools like State Trojan"},{"time":451065,"text":"to infect your computer with a Trojan,"},{"time":453601,"text":"which enables them\nto watch all your communication,"},{"time":457991,"text":"to listen to your online discussions,"},{"time":460832,"text":"to collect your passwords."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466556,"text":"Now, when we think deeper\nabout things like these,"},{"time":471800,"text":"the obvious response\nfrom people should be,"},{"time":477138,"text":"\"OK, well, that sounds bad,\nbut that doesn't really affect me,"},{"time":481404,"text":"because I'm a legal citizen."},{"time":483604,"text":"Why should I worry?\nBecause I have nothing to hide.\""},{"time":488113,"text":"And this is an argument\nwhich doesn't make sense."},{"time":491977,"text":"Privacy is implied."},{"time":494810,"text":"Privacy is not up for discussion."},{"time":499278,"text":"This is not a question"},{"time":501174,"text":"between privacy"},{"time":505747,"text":"against security."},{"time":508469,"text":"It's a question of freedom"},{"time":512048,"text":"against control."},{"time":514786,"text":"And while we might trust our governments\nright now, right here in 2011,"},{"time":521673,"text":"any rights we give away\nwill be given away for good."},{"time":525136,"text":"And do we trust, do we blindly trust,\nany future government,"},{"time":529741,"text":"a government we might have\n50 years from now?"},{"time":536200,"text":"And these are the questions"},{"time":539010,"text":"that we have to worry about\nfor the next 50 years."}]}]}